<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1065163 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Happy-Hour-Med.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="719" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Happy-Hour-Med.jpg 1280w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Happy-Hour-Med-640x360.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Happy-Hour-Med-1062x598.jpg 1062w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Happy-Hour-Med-320x180.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Happy-Hour-Med-281x158.jpg 281w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Happy-Hour-Med-562x316.jpg 562w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Happy-Hour-Med-531x299.jpg 531w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Happy-Hour-Med-487x274.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Happy-Hour-Med-974x547.jpg 974w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Happy-Hour-Med-600x337.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" />Sheraton Lagos Hotel has announced that for the month of November, there is something exciting for everyone. The General Manager Mr. Barry Curran said, “Our teams have organised great deals for everyone looking for relaxing and engaging experiences with friends and families.” The hotel will kick things off on November 19, by celebrating with all men, who dine with at the Pumpkin Leaf & Italian Restaurant, as it marks International Men’s Day. “Every man who dines with us will get a free beer,” Curran assured. November 28 is a double treat, as the hotel will mark world French Toast Day, alongside Thanksgiving. French toast will be available for breakfast; so all lovers of this sweet treat can indulge. “Our guests will also enjoy turkey on the roast with the stuffing and much more to celebrate thanksgiving with all our American friends and all those who follow the tradition,” he said. For Black Friday (Nov 29), which is everyone’s favorite non-holiday, the hotel will give a 20% discount on all purchases in all outlets, except the Pumpkin Leaf Restaurant. Though this discount cannot be applied with other discounts. “Our ‘Plan for More’ meetings and events promotion is still on. The promotion offers event organisers and meeting planners the chance to earn triple Marriott Bonvoy points when booking an event, meeting or a group stay at one of the participating hotels across Marriott International’s distinct portfolio in the region. In addition, the promotion offers 5% discount on the master bill for all eligible charges at participating hotels.” To receive triple points, bookings must be made before May 31, 2020, for meetings, events and group stays between September 15 and December 31, 2020. “We look forward to welcoming all our esteemed Patrons to a delightful November with us at Sheraton, where the world comes together and infuses the energy of our guests coming into our spaces,” Curran said.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .